                            <comment id="129751" author="bfaccini" created="Wed, 7 Oct 2015 20:12:08 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Finally, looks like the comment is outdated and that the ctime diff test has been changed by patch for &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-6213&quot; title=&quot;&amp;#39;tar -c&amp;#39; returns status 1 if HSM released files were encountered&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-6213&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-6213&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, which claims to allow for no ctime modification upon restore ...&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="129748" author="bfaccini" created="Wed, 7 Oct 2015 19:36:01 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;+1 at &lt;a href=&quot;https://testing.hpdd.intel.com/test_sets/65b541f0-6d13-11e5-bf10-5254006e85c2&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://testing.hpdd.intel.com/test_sets/65b541f0-6d13-11e5-bf10-5254006e85c2&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
It is the 10th failure since Sept 13th. All with the same &quot;restore changed ctime from X to Y&quot; and always with Y=X + 4/5s.&lt;br/&gt;
Having a look to sanity-hsm/test_24a, looks like the post-restore test of a ctime diff :&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;[ $ctime0 -eq $ctime1 ] ||
             error &quot;release changed ctime from $ctime0 to $ctime1&quot;
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;does not agree with previous comment :&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;# Restore should not change atime or mtime and should not
# decrease ctime.
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;So, is ctime expected to &quot;only&quot; grow after restore, and thus test must be changed accordingly, or not ?&lt;/p&gt;
</comment>
